entities.description: The utilization of professional counseling, medication, or other treatment for mental health, emotions, or behavior during the past 12 months.
The thought or feeling that a person should get professional counseling, medication, or other treatment for mental health, emotions, or behavior during the past 12 months.
The reasons why a person did not get additional professional counseling, medication, or other treatment for mental health, emotions, or behavior.
The perception that mental health treatment cost too much, resulting in unmet treatment needs.
The lack of health insurance coverage for mental health treatment, resulting in unmet treatment needs.

relationships.description: Indicates whether the respondent utilized mental health services during the past 12 months.
Indicates whether the respondent felt the need for mental health treatment but did not receive it.
Indicates the reasons why the respondent did not get additional mental health treatment.
Indicates that the high cost of treatment was a reason for unmet mental health treatment needs.
Indicates that the lack of health insurance coverage was a reason for unmet mental health treatment needs.
